This will also cause grub2-install to error out unless we uncomment and specify the GRUB_DEVICE=/dev/sdc3 in {{Path|/etc/default/grub}}.  When we googled around for this, we found a number of pages such as Fedora bug reports that suggested a patch with bash arrays and jiggered quotes in a grub2 script.  However it doesn't appear that this patch has gotten far enough upstream or resolved to everyone's liking for Gentoo stable to pick it up yet.

We also uncomment and force GRUB_TERM=console since other pages suggest that there may be issues with grub2 using a framebuffer and then running the proprietary nvidia-driver for X11 later on.  This may also be true for recent xf86-video-ati driver versions where we are activating a framebuffer before the GPU firmware gets loaded later on from {{Path|/lib/firmware}}.


